Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "reku" in different forms and positions:

1. *Rekoh* mu da dođe u utorak. (I told him to come on Tuesday.)
2. Sada *reči* više nije bilo moguće. (Now it was no longer possible to speak.)
3. Na kraju, *rekao* je da se slaže sa mnom. (In the end, he said he agreed with me.)
4. *Rečeno* je da će biti kiše sutra. (It was said that there will be rain tomorrow.)
5. Dok je ona *pričala*, ja sam samo ćutao. (While she was talking, I just stayed silent.)
6. Moram da *kažem*, ovo mi se uopšte ne dopada. (I have to say, I really don't like this.)
7. Ne znam šta da *pričam* s njim. (I don't know what to talk about with him.)
8. Oni su *rekli* da će doći u 8. (They said they would come at 8.)
9. *Reći* ću ti jednu tajnu. (I'll tell you a secret.)
10. Oni su *izgovorili* sve reči pogrešno. (They pronounced all the words wrong.)

(Note: The word "reku" is highlighted with an asterisk (*) in each sentence.)